1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
 It's really quite a profound prayer that we pray when we say, "Fill us up."

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,000
 It's a really beautiful thing if you look through Scripture.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
 If you look through the Old and the New Testament,

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:17,000
 and you see the number of times that God decides to come and meet His people

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
 and fill them in a particular way.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
 And oftentimes, particularly in the Old Testament,

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:28,000
 the Holy Spirit fell on particular people at particular times for particular purposes.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
 And then in the death and resurrection of Christ,

9
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
 and the tearing of the curtain in the temple,

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 the Spirit of God goes out to all people.

11
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
 To anyone who are willing to open their lives to Him and follow Him.

12
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:46,000
 And so throughout the Scripture story is this story of a God who longs to be with His people.

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
 And longs to meet His people where they're at and fill them

14
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:55,000
 so that they can become the very ones that He has always longed for them to be.

15
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
 And so as we were just worshipping just a moment ago,

16
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 and I was kind of walking around praying,

17
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
 I was saying to the Lord, "What is it that You want to fill us with, Lord?

18
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,000
 Like what is in your heart for this moment, particular people with a particular purpose

19
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 in this time in our city of Hong Kong?"

20
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
 And we say this often at the Vine, but if you're visiting here or you live here,

21
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
 no one is in Hong Kong right now by mistake, amen?

22
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:22,000
 And the Holy Spirit, God is doing something unique in this beautiful time

23
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
 that we have in our city right now.

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
 And so our prayer as a church needs to be,

25
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
 "Lord, how do You need to fill us?

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,000
 Like what is it that You want to impart,

27
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,000
 that You want to anoint into the church of Hong Kong in this hour and in this time?"

28
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
 And I was praying that for us, and I felt like the Lord say,

29
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:45,000
 "Andrew, I want to impart, I want to fill these people with boldness and courage."

30
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 Boldness and courage.

31
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:51,000
 I think we're standing at a time in Hong Kong's history

32
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
 where there's a window of grace that's before us.

33
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
 A window of opportunity for us to be what we've been talking about in this series,

34
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
 this idea of a public faith.

35
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:05,000
 To not take our belief in Jesus and the values that we have within that

36
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
 and hold it within ourselves.

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:13,000
 But to have the courage and the boldness to be those witnesses that Jesus said.

38
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,000
 He gathers His disciples around Him and He says,

39
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:21,000
 "You're going to receive power, and then you will become My witnesses."

40
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,000
 And this power that I think the Lord was speaking about in that moment

41
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:30,000
 is this beautiful sense of His love and His forgiveness and the boldness of the Spirit.

42
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,000
 And I think this is the time where He's saying, "Church, would you rise up?

43
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:42,000
 Would you be a prophetic voice into a city that desperately needs a story of hope?"

44
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
 And we've seen the economy rebound.

45
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 We've seen things happen in our city, which is a good thing.

46
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:54,000
 But scratch below the surface and there's still so much need here.

47
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
 There are so many questions still.

48
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
 So much anxiety and fear.

49
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:03,000
 And here we are gathered in a room like this, gathered online in this moment,

50
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:09,000
 and we're the ones that carry a message that brings hope.

51
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
 And the Lord says that there's one thing the church needs,

52
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
 boldness and courage for your family.

53
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:19,000
 Some of you in this room, you're first-generation Christians in your family.

54
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,000
 And somebody's brought you to Jesus, and you come into this loving relationship,

55
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,000
 and you long on your heart to see other people in your family come to Jesus.

56
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
 For some of you, it's your workplace.

57
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
 You're surrounded with amazing colleagues and people,

58
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,000
 but you're surrounded with them and you're thinking,

59
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 "Man, how can I share something of Jesus with them?"

60
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,000
 Maybe it's in your social context, in your relationships.

61
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:43,000
 It's different for all of us, but this boldness and this courage

62
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 to say, "I know and I have a relationship with someone

63
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:53,000
 that could make a difference in your life."

64
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,000
 And so I want to pray for you.

65
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,000
 I want to pray that you would receive boldness and courage today,

66
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:03,000
 that in this moment and throughout the time when we open Scripture,

67
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:08,000
 that you would feel an impartation, an anointing for boldness and courage

68
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:12,000
 in your sphere of influence like you've never felt before,

69
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:16,000
 and that we would see a rich harvest.

70
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:21,000
 Jesus says, "Put your hands on the plow and don't look back over your shoulder."

71
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,000
 And I pray for the courage that we would have to be the workers

72
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,000
 in the harvest field in this time. Amen?

73
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:32,000
 So if you're wanting to receive that sort of sense of anointing for you,

74
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:39,000
 whatever it might be, maybe just you can open your hands before you as I pray.

75
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:43,000
 Father, we've just been singing as the church community fill us up.

76
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 Lord, our hands are open before you now as we stand together

77
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,000
 as a church community now.

78
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:55,000
 And Lord, we ask for boldness and for courage.

79
00:04:55,000 --> 00:05:00,000
 And we ask for boldness and courage to give us a fire within us

80
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:07,000
 for the gospel, for the joy of being able to share the story of Jesus.

81
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:15,000
 Lord, we just confess that fear can so often grab a hold of our hearts.

82
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:20,000
 We confess that often it's easier for us to conform to culture

83
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,000
 than to stand against it.

84
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,000
 But Lord, we stand before you in this moment, having sung those words, fill us up.

85
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,000
 And Lord, we say, would you give us boldness? Would you give us courage?

86
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
 Would you fill us again with the hope of the gospel?

87
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 Would you fill us with your love, with your mercy, and with your grace?

88
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 And would you send us, Lord?

89
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:41,000
 We don't want to be people that experience something of Jesus

90
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
 gathered for 90 minutes.

91
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
 We want to be a sent people.

92
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
 You said to the disciples, "You will receive power and become my witnesses."

93
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,000
 That word means martyrs.

94
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:59,000
 Those that are willing to give of their life for the beauty

95
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:03,000
 that one would come into saving knowledge of Jesus Christ.

96
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:07,000
 Lord, would you give us the passion that you poured out onto the early church?

97
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:12,000
 Lord, we pray that the church of Hong Kong would have the same passion

98
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:16,000
 because we have the same spirit in us that raised Jesus from the dead.

99
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:25,000
 Lord, would you rebirth the gospel of resurrection hope in our city, Jesus?

100
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 So fill us.

101
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
 Fill us and send us.

102
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
 And would it be for your glory and your glory alone.

103
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 And we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

104
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
 Everyone says, "Amen."

105
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
 Amen.

106
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
 Have a seat. Have a seat.

107
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,000
 It's so good that you're here.

108
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,000
 My name is Andrew. I'm one of the pastors.

109
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:51,000
 If you're joining us online for the first time or if you're in this room in the overflow,

110
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
 joining us for the first time, we're so glad you're with us.

111
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,000
 We're in a series called Public Faith.

112
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:02,000
 And we're really unpacking through Scripture what we've just been praying about.

113
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:06,000
 This wonderful opportunity we have in the world right now

114
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 to see the gospel of Jesus take root and take hold like never before.

115
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:20,000
 And there's this really profound moment where the apostle Paul writes into the church in Rome.

116
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:24,000
 And in the very first chapter of his letter to the church in Rome,

117
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,000
 Paul writes a very short little verse.

118
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:32,000
 But it's a verse that really unpacks, I think, his manifesto for public faith.

119
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:37,000
 His manifesto for why we should live our faith publicly.

120
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,000
 And in so doing, he's, with this one little verse,

121
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:48,000
 trying to instill confidence and boldness and courage in the church in Rome.

122
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
 Now, the church in Rome, as far as we were aware,

123
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
 at the time of Paul's writing to it, was relatively small.

124
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:59,000
 In fact, from what we can tell, it was largely gathering in three small houses.

125
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:03,000
 It was three small house churches in the city of Rome.

126
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:07,000
 I wonder if you could imagine for a moment what it would have been like

127
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:12,000
 to be a Christian, to bear witness to the gospel of Jesus

128
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:19,000
 in the very epicenter of Greco-Roman empire and power.

129
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:26,000
 The whole of Rome was designed to speak forth a proclamation about power.

130
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:31,000
 The phrase, "All roads lead to Rome," was actually literally true.

131
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,000
 And everything funneled in the city, the architecture,

132
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,000
 the structure of the city in those days, all of it,

133
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,000
 the social structures and the social norms,

134
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 all of it was designed to bring you to the very center of that power,

135
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,000
 which was Caesar himself.

136
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:50,000
 And from Caesar, all of that power and that authority

137
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:54,000
 and the dominion of the empire went from Caesar back out

138
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
 to the rest of the Greco-Roman empire.

139
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 So imagine what it would be like for you to be somebody

140
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,000
 who was right there in the epicenter of that power,

141
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,000
 believing in a different kind of power.

142
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 Imagine how it must have felt to be embedded as a little piece of yeast

143
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:18,000
 in this massive amount of dough around you.

144
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,000
 And you would be forgiven for thinking that those people

145
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:26,000
 in those house churches, probably many of them new believers in Jesus,

146
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:30,000
 were pretty happy when they were in the safety and the security

147
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:35,000
 of those house church gatherings to profess their relationship with Jesus.

148
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
 But you could understand that as soon as they stepped out of there,

149
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:42,000
 their desire to want to keep pretty personal and pretty private

150
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 about that faith.

151
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:50,000
 And Paul, being the bold pastor that he is,

152
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:55,000
 writes to the church in Rome, a church he had never visited,

153
00:09:55,000 --> 00:10:00,000
 but he writes to the church in Rome and he says something to them

154
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,000
 that will shake that church like never before.

155
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 In fact, this thing that he says, and then he then unpacks it

156
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 throughout the rest of the letter, this thing that he said,

157
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 they didn't know it at the time, but it would become the catalyst

158
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:17,000
 to the greatest move of the Spirit of God in the church of Rome

159
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:21,000
 that it had ever experienced in its history up until that point.

160
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:25,000
 One little phrase.

161
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 You want to know what it is? Let me read it to you.

162
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:32,000
 This is Romans chapter 1, verse 16.

163
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:37,000
 Paul says, "I am not ashamed of the gospel

164
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
 because it is the power of God for the salvation

165
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:45,000
 of everyone who believes, first for the Jew,

166
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,000
 then for the Gentile."

167
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:53,000
 Paul writes into a church meeting behind closed doors

168
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:58,000
 and he says, "You have to understand

169
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:01,000
 that we are not to be ashamed of the gospel

170
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:04,000
 because it is the power of God for the salvation

171
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:08,000
 of everyone who believes."

172
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,000
 If you were to read this passage in the Greek,

173
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,000
 it's neatly written in two sections, the first half

174
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,000
 and the second half. I want to deal with both of those briefly.

175
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:20,000
 The first half, he says this, "I am not ashamed of the gospel,"

176
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:23,000
 or if you read it in the Greek, it reads more like this,

177
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:27,000
 "I am not shamed by the gospel."

178
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:32,000
 Paul is doing something very counter-cultural in this moment.

179
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,000
 He takes a word, this word "ashamed."

180
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 In the Greek, it was a word that was very central

181
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,000
 to the whole of the Greek and Roman culture and society.

182
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:46,000
 In fact, it was a word that was used very often in society.

183
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,000
 You have to understand that Greek and Roman society

184
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:52,000
 was built upon an honor-shame culture.

185
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,000
 An honor-shame culture was one where people lived their lives

186
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 very publicly and how they were seen publicly,

187
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:03,000
 their reputation, the way that others around them viewed them

188
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,000
 was very important. It was paramount to your success

189
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 in that city to have a good reputation or a good public persona

190
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:16,000
 and you did that through this process of honor and shame.

191
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:22,000
 Honor, quite literally, was the value of your worth in society

192
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:27,000
 and you gained honor by what you did and how you conducted yourself

193
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:32,000
 or perhaps the wealth that you had or the lineage that you were born into.

194
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:37,000
 So honor helped you to rise in status in society.

195
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,000
 Conversely, shame was the loss of honor.

196
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,000
 So honor could be gained but it could also be lost.

197
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:48,000
 And when you are shamed, it's because you had some honor before

198
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 but that honor is now gone.

199
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,000
 And when somebody was shamed in Greek or Roman society,

200
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,000
 it was almost always public humiliation.

201
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
 Some public rejection.

202
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,000
 And you could get shamed for a lot of different things.

203
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:07,000
 Maybe aligning yourself to somebody who is of a low class in society.

204
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 Maybe professing to have a belief system or a thought

205
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,000
 that was different from the societal norms.

206
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,000
 If you could make yourself more like the society around you,

207
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
 you would rise in honor.

208
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:25,000
 But as soon as you began to act, think, or be different to the society around you,

209
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
 then shame would come upon you.

210
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
 Now here's the powerful thing.

211
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:39,000
 The symbol of the greatest shame in Greek or Roman society was the crucifixion.

212
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:46,000
 The crucifixion was the highest punishment for the lowest level of status.

213
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:51,000
 And if anybody in your family had ever been crucified,

214
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:58,000
 the loss of face and the shame upon you as a family would last for generations.

215
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:05,000
 So crucifixion and the impact of that for shame and the loss of face

216
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 was central to the understanding of this Greek or Roman honor and shame culture.

217
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,000
 So could you imagine what it would be like to say,

218
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,000
 "I follow someone who was crucified."

219
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,000
 What you're essentially saying is,

220
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:22,000
 "I am following someone who has been deeply shamed and rejected,"

221
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:26,000
 which means by association, "I am also shamed."

222
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 And so you could forgive those people in the Church of Rome going,

223
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,000
 "Hey, I'm happy to confess Jesus as my Lord and Savior

224
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
 in the nice comfort of our home church,

225
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:40,000
 but as soon as I'm back outside there in Greek or Roman society,

226
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,000
 I don't want the shame of that relationship to still be on me.

227
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,000
 I don't want to be shamed by the gospel."

228
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,000
 Are you with me?

229
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,000
 No one is with me.

230
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,000
 Are you with me?

231
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 Paul writes into that and he says,

232
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,000
 "Here's the thing you need to know right up front."

233
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,000
 I've got a long letter and I'm going to unpack this in a lot of detail,

234
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
 but here's the summary of it.

235
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 "I am not ashamed of the gospel."

236
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:09,000
 In other words, "I am not shamed by the gospel,"

237
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,000
 which is incredibly powerful

238
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 because what he's trying to do is not just subvert a Greek or Roman system,

239
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,000
 but he's actually trying to show the church

240
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 why they should be bold and courageous

241
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:29,000
 because what they profess is actually the thing that that system desperately needs.

242
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,000
 Now, to understand that, you have to see the second side of the verse.

243
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:36,000
 In the Greek, it says something along the lines of like this,

244
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,000
 "Because," so I'm not ashamed of the gospel,

245
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:45,000
 "because it is the power of God for everyone in salvation, for everyone who believes."

246
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 Paul, once again, does something controversial.

247
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
 In the first half, he chooses his Greek word "ashamed,"

248
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
 which connected to the culture.

249
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,000
 He does the same sort of thing in the second half.

250
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:59,000
 He takes this word "power," which was central to the Roman church

251
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,000
 and the reality of that Roman culture.

252
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:06,000
 And he says, "You want to know what true power is?

253
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,000
 It is not what you have been told.

254
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:15,000
 It is not what everything in the city is trying and is designed to try to proclaim."

255
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,000
 He's saying, "Here's what the true power is.

256
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:22,000
 The gospel is true power, and the reason why

257
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 is because it turns this whole honor-shame system on its head."

258
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:34,000
 See, Paul, he understood this was the gospel.

259
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,000
 If he was standing right here, he would tell you this is the gospel.

260
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 That God had such a heart for the broken world around him,

261
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 that he didn't consider being acquainted with that power

262
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
 and that authority on high something to be grasped,

263
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 but he humbled himself, and he came here in this incarnation.

264
00:16:53,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 And through a place of humility and love, he allowed himself to be crucified.

265
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:08,000
 He allowed himself to experience the worst public social shame that you could experience.

266
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:13,000
 And the reason why he allowed himself to be shamed so much

267
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:18,000
 was that because three days later, God raised him from death to life,

268
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:23,000
 and in raising him back into life, God makes a statement over the world

269
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,000
 that there is no amount of shame anymore

270
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:31,000
 that can ever hold you back from the love of God.

271
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,000
 So he's saying, and this is really theologically quite beautiful,

272
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:38,000
 how he's taking Greek and Roman culture, and he's actually flipping it,

273
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:42,000
 because he's saying the thing that you think is the place of greatest shame

274
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:47,000
 is actually the very thing that gives the greatest freedom.

275
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 In other words, true power is not being released from shame and dishonor socially.

276
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 It's being released from shame and dishonor eternally.

277
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,000
 That's what happens on the cross.

278
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 That's what Jesus does.

279
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 He stands in the gap and takes all of the shame of sin on his shoulders,

280
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,000
 the dishonor of every sin ever committed.

281
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 He takes it upon himself, and in raising to new life,

282
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:19,000
 forgives that sin, is the one sacrifice that pays the price

283
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:25,000
 so that no one else has to suffer anymore under any shame, any dishonor,

284
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:30,000
 that even in the worst of our sin, we have a God who still loves.

285
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,000
 We have a God who has set us free,

286
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 and we have a God who's created a pathway by which we can go from our shame

287
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,000
 to eternal glory in him.

288
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
 So I am not ashamed of the gospel, Paul said,

289
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:54,000
 because it is the very power to set you free from the shame society is placing on you.

290
00:18:54,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 It's pretty cool, because this enables the church in Rome

291
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,000
 to begin to think about everything differently and begin to go,

292
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:09,000
 "Everybody around us is suffering with this system of honor and shame, honor and shame.

293
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 Everybody's so consumed by how they think of themselves and how they think of others,

294
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:18,000
 and they're stressed out, they're anxious, there's all this stuff going on,

295
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:23,000
 and we have the very message that sets them free from that.

296
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 But when we are ashamed of the gospel,

297
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 we keep the very message that can set them free simply to ourselves."

298
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 If I was to summarize these two sides of this really profound verse,

299
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 I would summarize it like this.

300
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 By emphasizing the gospel's divine power,

301
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 Paul is countering the perceived shame of a crucified Messiah

302
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:52,000
 and boldly challenging the honor-shame system of his day,

303
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 prioritizing, notice this, divine approval over cultural acceptance.

304
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 That is public faith.

305
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 Where we're going to prioritize divine approval over cultural acceptance.

306
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,000
 It should be not lost on us that here in Hong Kong,

307
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:18,000
 we're still living in an honor-shame society, are we not?

308
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 I mean, the idea of the loss of face is so embedded into our culture here in Hong Kong.

309
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 And perhaps you've experienced what it's like to lose face,

310
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 or perhaps someone in your family has experienced that,

311
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,000
 and you know what that social pull can be like.

312
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:37,000
 You know the brokenness of an honor-shame culture and society.

313
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,000
 So perhaps now more than ever,

314
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 this phrase that Paul writes to the church in Rome that was important for them 2,000 years ago

315
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 is even more important for the church of Hong Kong today.

316
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:51,000
 And perhaps it should be preached in every pulpit of every church in this city.

317
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 We are not ashamed of the gospel,

318
00:20:54,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 for it is the power of God for salvation for all who believe.

319
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:11,000
 The challenge we have, though, is that even in the desire to want to proclaim that,

320
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:14,000
 we recognize the fear inside of us.

321
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 We recognize the persecution.

322
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:18,000
 We recognize the weight and the heaviness of a society

323
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,000
 that can be so often against the very message that we hold.

324
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:25,000
 We worry about the loss of face.

325
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 We worry about the social impact.

326
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,000
 We worry about our jobs.

327
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,000
 And all of those things have weight,

328
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,000
 and all those things need to be held in balance with this.

329
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:38,000
 But ultimately, Paul writes to a church and says,

330
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,000
 "Do not think that you are shamed by this gospel.

331
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 In fact, remember that it is the very gospel that frees you from that shame."

332
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 And what a message of great hope that can be for here in Hong Kong today.

333
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:56,000
 But we have to realize that that hope is not a default reality.

334
00:21:56,000 --> 00:22:01,000
 What I mean by that is that that message has to go out.

335
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:07,000
 If all of it ever is is kept within the hearts and the lives of fiery Christians on a Sunday

336
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,000
 who raise their hands and sing loudly,

337
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 but never actually works out into their public sphere of their influence in the world,

338
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 then the very gift that God has given us to bring the hope to those that need it the most never gets heard.

339
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:23,000
 We need to preach it.

340
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Paul, actually, just a few chapters later in chapter 10, he says that exact thing.

341
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:31,000
 Let me read this to you in chapter 10, starting in verse 14.

342
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 He said, "How then can they call on the one that they have not believed in?

343
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 And how can they believe in the one whom they have not heard?

344
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 And how can they hear without someone preaching to them?"

345
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 And so Paul says, "Look, it's not just going to be a default reality that people realize,

346
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 'Oh, there's a God out there who has forgiven me of my shame and my brokenness and my sin,

347
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 and I can have relations with him and new life.'"

348
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 No, this needs to be communicated. It needs to be lived. It needs to be preached.

349
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 It's one thing to believe that you are not ashamed of the gospel

350
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:05,000
 or to even believe that it is the power of God to bring salvation to the world,

351
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 but it's a whole other thing to actually then preach it, to actually then live it,

352
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 to actually then want to proclaim it, want to reveal it

353
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:21,000
 in whatever creative, bold, beautiful ways that your life might be created to do that.

354
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:25,000
 That's a whole other thing. I'm challenged to say it this way.

355
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 We are the greatest of hypocrites.

356
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:33,000
 We're the greatest hypocrites in the world if on the one hand,

357
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:36,000
 we have this idea that we are not ashamed of the gospel,

358
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 but on the other hand, we still keep it private.

359
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:44,000
 That's hypocritical. We should be ashamed by that.

360
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 I mean, we shouldn't say, "Hey, I'm not ashamed of the gospel,"

361
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 and then never tell anyone about it. Those two things don't work together.

362
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:57,000
 And so Paul is saying, "Look, the first thing you have to understand,

363
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:03,000
 we are not ashamed by this gospel, for it is the power of God for salvation

364
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 for all who believe. The very thing that was the instrument of shame

365
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 has become the very thing that's broken shame."

366
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 That's good news. That's very, very good news.

367
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 And that's good news for Hong Kong at a time when I think Hong Kong needs some good news.

368
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,000
 I want you to have a look at this table behind me.

369
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:29,000
 This is the number of Christians in Hong Kong over the last decade,

370
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:33,000
 so 2015 through to 2025.

371
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:37,000
 Now, there's some encouragement in this graph, as you can probably see.

372
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:41,000
 Back 10 years ago, we had about a million Christians in Hong Kong,

373
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 Protestant and Catholic, which was about 13.9% of the population at that time.

374
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:52,000
 Today, in 2025, we have roughly about 1.4 million Protestants and Catholics in Hong Kong,

375
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:56,000
 which comes to about 19% of the population today.

376
00:24:56,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 So actually, in the last decade, Christianity in our city has grown by 40%.

377
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 That's pretty good news. I don't think that's great news,

378
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 but that's pretty good news, right? Like 40% is decent.

379
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 We're heading in the right direction.

380
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:11,000
 You'll notice that the population of Hong Kong Christian is going,

381
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,000
 and the population of Hong Kong is going down.

382
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,000
 We're going up, they're going down. I don't know what's going on there.

383
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:18,000
 One day we'll meet, you know, in the middle.

384
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 But there's some good news in that graph.

385
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:25,000
 But here's the statistic of that graph that moves me the most.

386
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:29,000
 There's still 80% of the people of our city that don't know Jesus.

387
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:33,000
 80% when the church has been in Hong Kong for 100 years.

388
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,000
 When the church has been in our city for 100 years,

389
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:40,000
 and there's still 80% of the people in the city that don't profess Jesus

390
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:43,000
 as their Lord and Savior, we have to be honest with ourselves

391
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 and say, "Are we actually ashamed of the gospel?"

392
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:54,000
 Six years ago, God lit a fire under us here at the Vine

393
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 when it comes to this idea of sharing the gospel or living

394
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,000
 or being the gospel more in our city.

395
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:05,000
 He challenged us in how we view what it is to do church, to be church, to have church.

396
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:08,000
 And He challenged us that we need to start thinking of church differently

397
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:14,000
 from one building in one static location to church being the people of God

398
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 who spread out in their spheres of influence around their city

399
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:21,000
 a little bit like a river that flows through the city.

400
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:25,000
 So you've probably heard us talk about the river model over the last six years.

401
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:31,000
 This beautiful idea that we can take the gospel into all of our spheres of influence

402
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:36,000
 like that river watering every part of our city for the glory of God.

403
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:41,000
 It's a beautiful, bold, courageous vision that can only happen

404
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:46,000
 if God stirs something within us and in our hearts.

405
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:49,000
 Because of this vision six years ago, we began to think and pray

406
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,000
 as a leadership around church planting.

407
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:54,000
 Because when God says, "Hey, this is how I want you to be,"

408
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:59,000
 a river flowing in the city, we began to think, "Well, we need to be flowing in the city."

409
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:02,000
 And that means in our workplaces, and it means as a people,

410
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:07,000
 but it also means that we need to express ourselves across the city in different ways.

411
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:11,000
 And you'll know three years ago, we started our first church plant.

412
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:15,000
 We planted in Yulong, and Tim and Ivan as leaders there,

413
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,000
 and the other staff there have done a tremendous job over the last three years.

414
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:24,000
 There's probably around about 300 people that meet regularly on a Sunday in Yulong.

415
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,000
 We have service in Cantonese and in English,

416
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:29,000
 and a lot of those 300 people are new believers.

417
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,000
 People have come to Christ because we planted something there.

418
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,000
 We've reached out with the gospel.

419
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 We believe that we're not going to be ashamed of it

420
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:41,000
 and that we're going to bring an expression of it to a cultural group of people that need it most.

421
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:45,000
 Well, today, I'm really excited that we're making another big announcement.

422
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:48,000
 This is going to be a Sunday where you're going to look back in a few years' time and go,

423
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:50,000
 "I was there that day."

424
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:53,000
 And to help make that big announcement,

425
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:58,000
 I'm really excited to invite to the stage two people that have been very central

426
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:02,000
 to the life and growth and development of the Vine over the last 18 years.

427
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:04,000
 They've held staff roles here.

428
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:08,000
 They've been volunteers within our ministry, but they have a heart.

429
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 I think they're like the pools of the pool to Rome.

430
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,000
 They are like them.

431
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,000
 They're like pool to Hong Kong in this time.

432
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:19,000
 I know for 100% certainty that they are not ashamed of the gospel.

433
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:21,000
 So to help us make this announcement, can you put your hands together

434
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
 as we invite Sidney and Vivian Yip?

435
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 Good morning, Church.

436
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:38,000
 Well, thank you, Andrew.

437
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:43,000
 Well, we are going to share some of our stories and hope that they find resonance in you

438
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:47,000
 before we do the announcement part of it.

439
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:51,000
 My name is Sidney, and this is Vivian.

440
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:59,000
 We just celebrated our 34th wedding anniversary.

441
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:03,000
 We've been in the Vine community for the past 18 years.

442
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 I have the privilege to serve in the eldership for nine years,

443
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 including five years as chairman of the board.

444
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:15,000
 But I'd like to rewind it to 50 years ago.

445
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:19,000
 Okay, when I entered into my secondary school,

446
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 and the name of the secondary school is Yinghua College,

447
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 which literally means Anglo-Chinese school.

448
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:31,000
 Yinghua, Siyun.

449
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 Now, on that very first day when I started, I literally cried my eyes out

450
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:41,000
 because that was my third choice of school.

451
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 But God had a greater plan.

452
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:50,000
 I only subsequently knew that Yinghua was first founded in 1818,

453
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 more than 200 years ago, by the London Missionary Society.

454
00:29:55,000 --> 00:30:00,000
 Their vision was to educate Chinese students,

455
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:04,000
 teaching literacy, morals, and Christian values.

456
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:09,000
 But most of all, they would want them to become agents

457
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:13,000
 to bring the gospel to China.

458
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:18,000
 Now, that seed of vision continued for over 200 years,

459
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 and I'm always amazed how more than half of my classmates

460
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:26,000
 come to faith during our school years,

461
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 many of whom became pastors, elders, leaders in Christian NGOs,

462
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:36,000
 or serving in their own rights in unique manners.

463
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:39,000
 I am also one of the first.

464
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 Though somehow along the way, I backslid in my faith commitments,

465
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:46,000
 I went on to pursue some of my own dreams,

466
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 and drifted away from faith for more than 15 years.

467
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 But God is gracious.

468
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 As if in Genesis, Joseph say, "Well, you intended to."

469
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 "Well, I intended to pursue my own dreams."

470
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 But God intended it for good,

471
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 to accomplish what is now being done,

472
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:08,000
 the saving of many lives.

473
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,000
 So, it was actually some time down the road

474
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 when we moved over to Singapore

475
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 that my passion to serve Him reignited.

476
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 So, on one of the weekends,

477
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:23,000
 while I was working as a medical profession in Singapore,

478
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 one of my patients left into a sudden coma.

479
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 So, his wife was devastated.

480
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 I wanted to bring some comfort to her,

481
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
 but she was a Mandarin speaker.

482
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 So, I called up my church pastors,

483
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 as usual, as many of you would have done.

484
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 But on a Sunday or Saturday, I can't remember exactly,

485
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 no one was really available.

486
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 So, I was tasked by the leader that,

487
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 "Well, why not go and reach out,

488
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 share comfort and good news with her?"

489
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 So, the backdrop is we really came from

490
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:59,000
 an English-speaking congregation.

491
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:04,000
 But I recall, well, that some time ago,

492
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:06,000
 that was in the '70s,

493
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 we were taught Mandarin in Yinghua College.

494
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 So, I picked up some of those

495
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 and shared a word of encouragement.

496
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 Now, the important matter was,

497
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:24,000
 well, I realized that God could be using me

498
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:29,000
 to reach out to Chinese-speaking people.

499
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 Now, as we shared earlier on,

500
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,000
 we actually returned to Hong Kong

501
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,000
 and joined Divine for the past two decades.

502
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 Actually, through the years,

503
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 we saw God's hands working in this church,

504
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 building something really beautiful,

505
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:46,000
 especially in the reaching out to Chinese speakers.

506
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 Looking back, I can see the seed planted in me

507
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 50 years ago is continuing to grow.

508
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 And I want to be faithful to God and His calling.

509
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:02,000
 For me, my journey began in Singapore

510
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 more than 25 years ago.

511
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:09,000
 My family moved there when I was in mid-30s,

512
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:12,000
 and hardly knew anyone there.

513
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 One day at the pool,

514
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 while our kids were in the swimming class,

515
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:19,000
 another mom began chatting with me,

516
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 and we quickly connected.

517
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 Through her friendship and outreach,

518
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 I was welcomed into her home church,

519
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 and that eventually became my community.

520
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 I was not treated as a foreigner or an outsider.

521
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:38,000
 I was accepted and loved.

522
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:43,000
 And there, I accepted Christ as my own Savior.

523
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:47,000
 Our marriage grew stronger,

524
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:49,000
 and our family became closer.

525
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 We opened our home for small groups,

526
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 and we were tremendously blessed.

527
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 And then we led small groups,

528
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:02,000
 including family groups with children ministry.

529
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:06,000
 That is one of our family groups

530
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 that was in Singapore years ago.

531
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 Yeah, and our lives were indeed transformed.

532
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:19,000
 I also got involved in the Inner Healing and Deliverance ministry,

533
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 as well as the Pastoral Care ministry.

534
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:25,000
 Over these 10 years,

535
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:28,000
 we witnessed our home church

536
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 has planted at least two more churches.

537
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 When my family moved back from Singapore,

538
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:39,000
 I finished my theological studies in Hong Kong.

539
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 But even before I knew exactly

540
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:46,000
 what God wanted me to do and serve,

541
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:51,000
 God was really and already leading me.

542
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,000
 He led us to the vine,

543
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 and I joined the pastoral staff team in 2014.

544
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 Over the years, I am honored

545
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 being part of this wonderful senior leadership team,

546
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:09,000
 and I am passionate to lead the Chinese ministry,

547
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:12,000
 both the Cantonese and the Mandarin communities,

548
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:17,000
 and more recently, leading the restoration ministry.

549
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:22,000
 But I would like to flash back in 2014

550
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
 at the English and Cantonese Alva Retreat

551
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 in the West Ark of Ma Wan.

552
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:33,000
 God gave me a vision during worship.

553
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 I saw dazzling lights spread across the land,

554
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:42,000
 shining outward in all directions.

555
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 I did not fully understand them,

556
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:48,000
 but my heart sensed it was the call

557
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 to reach further the Chinese community.

558
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 What we began as a home group of 20

559
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:00,000
 has grown into a vibrant Chinese ministry.

560
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,000
 And you will see here is a picture

561
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 of our Cantonese community back in 2018.

562
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 And now today, my heart still believes God is saying,

563
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,000
 "There is more to come."

564
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 And I want to avail myself to love the people

565
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 that God put into our lives.

566
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 So what is this more?

567
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:29,000
 The vine has embraced the Reformation for six, seven years,

568
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:32,000
 and I pray that this will continue to inspire us

569
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:36,000
 to see that we can be part of something even bigger,

570
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 which is still unfolding.

571
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:43,000
 Today we are excited to announce that Vivian and I,

572
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,000
 together with the leadership of the vine,

573
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 are sensing a call for us to move out

574
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:54,000
 and plant a fresh kind of missional outreach vine church

575
00:36:54,000 --> 00:37:00,000
 in the North Metropolis area of Hong Kong.

576
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:03,000
 Now the call of this new river initiative is distinct.

577
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:08,000
 It would be sharing the love of Christ with Chinese speakers,

578
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 Mandarin and Cantonese included,

579
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:14,000
 in a way that encourages real spiritual growth

580
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:20,000
 and builds loving, Christ-centered communities without walls.

581
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:26,000
 Our mission is to create a network of these caring communities

582
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:31,000
 woven throughout the North Metropolis of Hong Kong.

583
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:39,000
 And we hope and we dream that there will be planting church, planting churches.

584
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,000
 So they aren't just churches in buildings,

585
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:45,000
 they are churches in homes, workplaces, and neighborhoods,

586
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:49,000
 everywhere people gather and live their daily lives.

587
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:51,000
 And here's the real beauty.

588
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:54,000
 As we plant new churches and communities,

589
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,000
 they will in turn plant more.

590
00:37:56,000 --> 00:38:00,000
 And this multiplication will help us establish a sustainable,

591
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:04,000
 vibrant gospel presence across the region.

592
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:07,000
 It's not just about maintaining what's here.

593
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:10,000
 It's about growing and spreading out

594
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:14,000
 so that we may reach more lives for Jesus.

595
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:20,000
 Even in John 15, it is read this way,

596
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:26,000
 "Every branch that does bear fruit, he prunes,

597
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:30,000
 he prunes, so that it may be even more fruitful."

598
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:33,000
 And we yearn to be even more fruitful.

599
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:36,000
 But then why focus on the North Metropolis?

600
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:42,000
 So for obvious reasons, it is one of Hong Kong's fastest growing areas.

601
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:47,000
 The North Metropolis actually includes areas beyond Shaanxi, Fanning, Yunnan,

602
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:52,000
 but also Tianshui and all the new zones in between, including Kutong, Shantin.

603
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:58,000
 And over the next decade, more than one million new residents will move in,

604
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:02,000
 bringing the total population over there to 2.5 million.

605
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,000
 Many will be new families, professionals,

606
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:11,000
 people from Hong Kong who are relocated from their original residence,

607
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:15,000
 and also new residents from mainland China.

608
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:20,000
 Now while some local churches in Hong Kong are beginning to venture into this new area,

609
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:27,000
 the overall landscape is that the people are still underserved by churches.

610
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:30,000
 Some places are instead blank slates.

611
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:35,000
 And what an opportunity for the gospel to take root and flourish.

612
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:39,000
 Yes, what excites me most are the people,

613
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:45,000
 new neighbors, new families, and who do not yet know Jesus.

614
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:51,000
 Yeah, but Jesus loves them regardless, no less than how He loves us.

615
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:58,000
 God has invited us to go to them, to be His hands and feet in this new area,

616
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:01,000
 Northern Metropolis.

617
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:04,000
 Malachi 4, 5 and 6,

618
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:11,000
 "See, I will send the prophet Elijah to you before that great and dreadful day of the Lord comes.

619
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:15,000
 He will turn the hearts of the parents to their children

620
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:18,000
 and the hearts of the children to their parents."

621
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:23,000
 At the Vine Restoration, we have heard many powerful testimonies

622
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:26,000
 from participants in their courses.

623
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:30,000
 Not only did they experience their personal heart healing,

624
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:35,000
 but also the restoration of broken relationships.

625
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:40,000
 Reconciliation is still happening in homes between spouses,

626
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:43,000
 between parents and the children.

627
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:51,000
 God is truly at work turning hearts back to Him and also to one another.

628
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:54,000
 Let's see, Mark 4, 35,

629
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:57,000
 "Let us go over to the other side.

630
00:40:57,000 --> 00:41:01,000
 Despite the initial success and all reasons to stay,

631
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:07,000
 Jesus called His disciples to venture into new territories

632
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:11,000
 and potentially hostile ministry grounds.

633
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:16,000
 Likewise, our calling is to cross over,

634
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:21,000
 go further and step into this new uncharted

635
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:27,000
 because many lives are waiting to encounter Jesus,

636
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:31,000
 His presence, His love, His hope."

637
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:37,000
 Do we dare to believe that God is indeed leading the Vine into this uncharted area

638
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:42,000
 as part of the Kingdom's advancement in His grand plan for Hong Kong?

639
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
 We felt led by the Spirit to narrow our focus to reaching out to local Cantonese speakers

640
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:55,000
 or Mandarin speakers who have settled or are settling to integrate with the broader community here in Hong Kong.

641
00:41:55,000 --> 00:42:01,000
 We want to be part of the new and developing community that will grow and mature in years to come.

642
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:10,000
 Still, we want to start now, operating from possibly Shangshui as a base for our outreach efforts,

643
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:13,000
 discipleship and small group developments.

644
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:19,000
 In fact, while the real estate sentiment was really at rock bottom last year,

645
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:27,000
 our family made a small, bold move to move from the island side to the new territories.

646
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:37,000
 I used to walk, no, I used to take three minutes lift, okay, from the hospital quarters to the hospital,

647
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:40,000
 which is right opposite, to attend to my patients.

648
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:45,000
 These days I drove 50 to 60 minutes to commute to work.

649
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:53,000
 But now we have the benefit of reaching North Metropolis in 20 minutes and the border in 25 minutes.

650
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:59,000
 Well, we are convinced that God will honor our commitments to avail ourselves.

651
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:05,000
 We want to develop small groups as the basis for many interlinking building blocks

652
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,000
 for fellow believers who may be dispersed over a wide stretch of land throughout North Metropolis.

653
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:23,000
 And yet, we desire to be united with the vine as we share the pulpit messages from the vine as anchors for our Sunday gatherings.

654
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:33,000
 We may be starting small, but we plant the seeds, water the plants, and may God grow and transform lives.

655
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:40,000
 We pray that we'll continue to see lives being renewed and transformed through this church plant.

656
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:46,000
 Earlier, I shared my faith journey began in an English-speaking community.

657
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:50,000
 My theological training was entirely English-based.

658
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:59,000
 I had no connections with the local churches in Hong Kong and little understanding of the religious sentiments in China.

659
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:07,000
 I didn't even have the Christian vocabulary or prayer language in Cantonese and Mandarin.

660
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:18,000
 So, when God gave me that vision more than 10 years ago to reach out to the local Chinese community, I felt completely unqualified.

661
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:26,000
 I felt like Jeremiah in chapter 1 saying, "I do not know how to speak.

662
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:33,000
 How possibly could I serve the Chinese?"

663
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:47,000
 I saw all my inadequacies, my lack of fluency, my unfamiliarity of the local Christian culture, my limited experience, the list goes on.

664
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:50,000
 My heart was overwhelmed.

665
00:44:50,000 --> 00:45:03,000
 But looking back now, I realize those places of weakness were where God was inviting me to surrender, to surrender, to surrender.

666
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:15,000
 What I saw as a limitation, God embraced as an invitation, an invitation for His presence to reach us and to lead,

667
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:27,000
 His strength to see us through and to make known His love for the Chinese, not by my ability, but by His calling and grace.

668
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:41,000
 And now, as we step into this next uncharted season as a church, we feel that same call again to enter a new frontier with boldness, courage, and humility,

669
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:53,000
 to reach out to the Chinese in a new context, in a new era, not from a place of confidence, but from vulnerability, authenticity, and love.

670
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:57,000
 Do we have all the answers? No.

671
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:05,000
 But we are going, not because the path is clear, but because the Spirit is leading.

672
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:14,000
 We dare to believe when we do God's work in God's way and in God's timing, we always see God's fruits.

673
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:17,000
 So how should this congregation respond?

674
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:23,000
 Number one, well, don't belittle yourself as an English speaker.

675
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:33,000
 Prayerfully discern that God could be igniting a passion for you to reach out to the Chinese speakers in the land.

676
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:43,000
 And then you think of your time, your talents, and your treasures that God has entrusted to you, which you may contribute to this vision.

677
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:52,000
 The operating model of this New River Initiative is that lots of the ministry will be led by volunteers and lay leaders.

678
00:46:52,000 --> 00:47:00,000
 And I'm privileged to be one of these paid, no, not paid, lay leaders.

679
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:07,000
 Well, we want to take the time to grow the community in relationship to discipleship and in readiness to reach out.

680
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:16,000
 While we discern and identify the appropriate venue for gathering, both in the interim as well as the midterm,

681
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:22,000
 when more of the northern metropolis facilities and venues may become available.

682
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:24,000
 Yeah, so what next?

683
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:31,000
 Next Sunday, after three services, please join us in the info booth outside the auditorium.

684
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:43,000
 We would love to connect with you, answer your questions, and perhaps, you know, might help you to find out a little bit more, explore a little bit more of the church plant.

685
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:54,000
 And then on another Sunday, November 2nd, we will host a launch gathering in the first floor mini hall at 415.

686
00:47:54,000 --> 00:48:03,000
 We will share more about our hearts, the vision, the mission, the practical next steps, and how we can forward together.

687
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:11,000
 So, after the launch gathering, we will begin this bi-weekly gatherings.

688
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:23,000
 Yeah, though we have not known the gathering place, but we will come and pray together to build deeper community and prepare what's next.

689
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:39,000
 Well, we've been wrestling on this matter for the past two years, and we come back again and again to the honest question, whether we are fast enough.

690
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:42,000
 What do you mean by fast?

691
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:53,000
 To be faithful in our calling to serve God, to be available, to be present with His people, even though when it's not convenient.

692
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:57,000
 Anyway, you know that northern Metropolis is very far away.

693
00:48:57,000 --> 00:49:02,000
 And my own challenge is, am I really available?

694
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:10,000
 Are we submissive to the guidance of the Holy Spirit while we don't have the grand plan or the book prints?

695
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:21,000
 And are we ourselves leading transformed life in our inner being, as well as be transformative in our outward living?

696
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:31,000
 Now, if that resonates with you, we would love to have you join me with us on this fast track.

697
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:33,000
 God is already moving in the northern Metropolis.

698
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:37,000
 Could He be inviting you to join Him?

699
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:48,000
 Perhaps He's calling you to be part of the team, a future financial supporter, or even someone who can offer a venue for ministry gatherings.

700
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:52,000
 Or maybe He's placed other resources for you to contribute.

701
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:54,000
 You may be living in Shaanxi.

702
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,000
 In whatever ways, God may be leading you.

703
00:49:56,000 --> 00:50:06,000
 We're excited to look forward to seeing how God brings together His people to serve Him together as a team.

704
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:18,000
 Yes, yes, as we, yeah, as today's sermon, as Andrew preached, that we as a church are not ashamed of the gospel.

705
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:25,000
 During the worship, we have the song saying that we as a church decided to follow Jesus.

706
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:26,000
 What happened?

707
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:30,000
 No turning back, but forward.

708
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:32,000
 Be mindful.

709
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,000
 No turning back.

710
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:46,000
 So, we pray that by the Spirit moving in our hearts that we will respond to His calling in obedience.

711
00:50:46,000 --> 00:51:00,000
 Alright, and we would like to take a moment to thank all our friends, families, and also our mentors in other places who are watching online.

712
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:10,000
 So, thank you so much because you have been walking with us and support us with so much love in our journey.

713
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:11,000
 Thank you.

714
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:19,000
 Well, let's step into this dream together for the glory of God and for the blessing of the Chinese-speaking people in our city.

715
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:20,000
 Yeah.

716
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:26,000
 [Applause]

717
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:27,000
 Thank you.

718
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:29,000
 So excited.

719
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:30,000
 Yes.

720
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:32,000
 I'm kind of emotional like you are.

721
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:33,000
 I know you two are sweating.

722
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:35,000
 I was sweating too.

723
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:39,000
 This is something that not just Sidney and Vivian are doing.

724
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:43,000
 Obviously, they're going to be looking for people here to be a part of this journey with them.

725
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:46,000
 But actually, this church plant is something the Vine is doing.

726
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:48,000
 It's something we're doing as the community of God.

727
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:50,000
 We're planting another church in our city.

728
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:51,000
 Amen?

729
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:53,000
 It's incredibly exciting.

730
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:57,000
 And so, we want to just come around these guys and just stand with them and pray for them.

731
00:51:57,000 --> 00:52:03,000
 There's going to be many things in the months ahead that will keep you updated on the progress of all of this and ways that you can be involved.

732
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:11,000
 But today, it's about just praying, releasing you guys into this vision, and us as a church saying, "We're doing this together."

733
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:13,000
 So, can I invite you all to stand with me?

734
00:52:13,000 --> 00:52:15,000
 And we're going to stretch out our hands.

735
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:22,000
 And I'm going to invite pastors and elders and others that are available here to come as well and just lay hands on these guys.

736
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:26,000
 Let's stretch out our hands.

737
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:31,000
 Father, we just stand before you as a church community grateful.

738
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:37,000
 Grateful that in our own little way, we're declaring we're not ashamed of the gospel in Hong Kong.

739
00:52:37,000 --> 00:52:43,000
 And we thank you that there's that 80% of harvest field just right out there.

740
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:51,000
 And we thank you for this discerned call that we as an eldership and leadership have had to the northern metropolis part of our city.

741
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:55,000
 And we thank you that you've birthed that vision inside of Sydney and Vivian.

742
00:52:55,000 --> 00:53:06,000
 And Lord, we get to stand now as a church community just in prayer, in support, and in hope that these guys would, with their team,

743
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:12,000
 and those that come alongside of them in this season, see an incredible fruit.

744
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:17,000
 Lord, we want to pray into the kingdom. Hundreds of people would.

745
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:21,000
 We want to pray that they would plant churches that plant churches.

746
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:30,000
 We want to pray that you would place an anointing upon them where their focus is not on their seating capacity, but their sending capacity.

747
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:41,000
 We want to pray, Lord, that the power of God, this divine power to see salvation come, would be at the forefront of everything that they do.

748
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:46,000
 Lord, we want to pray that we would see the needle moved in our city.

749
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:50,000
 Many, many people coming to Christ Jesus.

750
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:54,000
 And Lord, we pray for this northern metropolis church plant.

751
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:57,000
 Lord, we have so many questions that are yet to be answered.

752
00:53:57,000 --> 00:54:05,000
 But Lord, I thank you for the faithfulness of these two to say that even without the answers, this is an uncharted season that the vine is in.

753
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:15,000
 And we're willing to be uncharted adventurers on uncharted waters, going with the wind of the spirit, even though not all the answers are there.

754
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:22,000
 Lord, I pray that that would inspire every person in this room as they think about their own life and their own situations.

755
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:26,000
 And Lord, we just thank you that your hand is upon this in a beautiful way.

756
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,000
 And we pray all this in Jesus name.

757
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:35,000
 Everyone says, can we give these guys a round of applause?

758
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:39,000
 And I want to just finish. We're just going to respond in worship in a second.

759
00:54:39,000 --> 00:54:42,000
 But I want to just finish by by challenging and praying for you.

760
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:45,000
 This is a plant that we're doing as a whole church.

761
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:58,000
 But today's message about not being ashamed of the gospel, this fervency, this urgency for living a public faith in your sphere of influence is for you.

762
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:01,000
 It's not just for Big Ben in Sydney. It's not just for the leadership of the church.

763
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:04,000
 It's for every single one of us.

764
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:08,000
 And maybe there's an area in your life, whether that's your family, your workplace,

765
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:15,000
 maybe a situation where you're planted a sphere of influence that you have where what you're hearing today resonates also with you.

766
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:19,000
 Or perhaps you feel the challenge that Paul brought the church in Rome,

767
00:55:19,000 --> 00:55:23,000
 a church where you could understand that they would want to hide.

768
00:55:23,000 --> 00:55:34,000
 And Paul's saying, no, no, we can't hide because we've got the very hope in us that breaks the shame that the culture has placed around us.

769
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:42,000
 And I want to pray for you that you would have a boldness and a courage in the gospel of Jesus Christ like never before.

770
00:55:42,000 --> 00:55:53,000
 And I want to pray that you would look at your family and your workplace and your sphere of influence, not with, oh man, I just don't think anyone's going to come to Jesus.

771
00:55:53,000 --> 00:56:01,000
 But with what an opportunity I have to just do the small thing I can to share the hope of Christ,

772
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:08,000
 even if it's just with one person and believe that God can do what I cannot do.

773
00:56:08,000 --> 00:56:10,000
 You're not responsible for saving anyone.

774
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:12,000
 That's Jesus's role.

775
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:15,000
 But you have been called to preach.

776
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:16,000
 Let me pray for you.

777
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:22,000
 Father, I thank you that Lord in this joy of the gospel that is inside of us,

778
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:27,000
 you would open our mouths to preach boldly and courageously like never before.

779
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:31,000
 You would open up our hands to work for the gospel like never before.

780
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:39,000
 Our feet to be the beautiful good news that takes the gospel to places where it currently is not being heard.

781
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:44,000
 I pray that our lifestyle would reveal the values in the heart of you.

782
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:54,000
 And I pray that we would do this in that boldness and courage, not because we have all the answers like Vivian and Sidney said, but simply because we are cool.

783
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:57,000
 We thank you for this in Jesus name.

784
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:58,000
 Everyone says, Amen.

785
00:56:58,000 --> 00:56:59,000
 Let's worship together.

786
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:09,000
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

